  <title class="- topic/title ">Set Up the Final Pre-Launch</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">As you prepare to launch your campaign,
	 you must set up the final pre-launch. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <steps id="steps_8D7E45C5A3BC48C7818FE9EE1784E661" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_BA959C5D3EE24E19BBD85EC256C616B5" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Copy the validated campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">This ensures your report data includes only
				future visits. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_C08689669F3A40AD9D62D11745096427" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Edit the copied campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <substeps id="substeps_96F856922A3946F29A3C379A74D561CD" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
          <substep id="substep_BB8BF9186D9141BCBB81B1A1601391A4" class="- topic/li task/substep ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the exclusive targeting
				  rule. 
				</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep id="substep_70ABCCC50B9B42AB88BDEB97C136B706" class="- topic/li task/substep ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Rename the campaign as needed. 
				</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep id="substep_4E03BFB9645646A7955A57D683648200" class="- topic/li task/substep ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Update campaign dates to match
				  your campaign strategy. 
				</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
              <p class="- topic/p ">
                <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tip:</b> You are not required to
					 enter an end date. Monitor the campaign traffic and manually deactivate it when
					 you have selected a winner. This ensures you control the campaign shut-off,
					 even if it is later than you expect. 
				  </p>
            </stepresult>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step id="step_0A94DF5C2ACB410F982511B8AE295D97" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If there are other active campaigns
			 sharing mboxes with the new campaign, 
			 <xref href="c_Understanding_Campaign_Priority.xml#concept_605FD7C4E2E14D2384487AFBA7067DF2" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">set campaign
				priority</xref> as needed. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">If you see an mbox collision notice or shared
				location notice under the mbox selection, then the mbox you selected is used in
				another campaign. Click the link in the message to see the other campaigns and
				their statuses. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_3BE42B61F59A4C1BA71ED8B74C32E650" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Save changes. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_527BF3C1476643158F8127F4CA374474" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Just before approval, you might want
			 to select the 
			 <xref href="t_Ignoring_Visits_from_Your_Browser.xml#task_460FEEEE3B7141DEB9162348E6682EB9" type="task" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">ignore visits
				from your browser</xref> setting. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
